    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Edward M. House</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="to"
                            >Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-28">October 28,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Things are moving so rapidly that the question of a place for the Peace
                    Conference is upon us. The French are urging Paris. The Belgians, Brussels. The
                    only objection to Paris is that if a sharp difference should arise between one
                    of the Allies and the French it might be embarrassing. Otherwise it is
                    desirable. Will you not advise me as to your preference.</p>
                <p>The Supreme War Council will not meet until Wednesday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
